Package: fda.vi
Title: Functional Data Analysis using Variational Inference
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Camila", "de Souza", ,"camila.souza@uwo.ca", role = "cre"),
    person("Stephen", "Kinsey", role = "aut"),
    person("Ana Carolina", "da Cruz", role = "aut"),
    person("Pedro Henrique", "Toledo Oliveira Sousa", role = "aut"))
Maintainer: Camila de Souza <camila.souza@uwo.ca>
Description: Implements a variational Expectation-Maximization (VEM) algorithm
    for smoothing one or multiple functional observations via basis function
    selection. The algorithm estimates all model parameters simultaneously and
    automatically, while accounting for within-curve correlation. The approach
    provides a flexible and computationally efficient framework for smoothing
    correlated functional data.
